            <strong>
            🇪🇺 European stocks climb as US and Russia discuss Ukraine ceasefire</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">European stocks reached record highs on Tuesday. <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-19-02-2025-wn1-3-equities-rallied-on-optimism" target="_blank">Equities rallied on optimism</a> related to the end of the Ukraine war after renewed diplomatic talks between the United States and Russia. The Stoxx 600 Index rose 0.3% at the end of trading day, while the Euro Stoxx 50 reached an all-time high. The United States and Russia are in active talks, and a summit between President Trump and President Putin is expected. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Despite the rally, some analysts maintain their cautious outlook. Panmure Liberum strategist Joachim Klement warned that despite the ongoing talks, obstacles remain in the way of a ceasefire, including the need to secure Ukraine’s agreement with any proposed resolution.</p>
        </mj-text>
